[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":287},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2021\u002F03\u002F26\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2021\u002F03\u002F26\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2021\u002F03\u002F26\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2021\u002F03\u002F26\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix\u002F":262,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2021\u002F03\u002F26\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix\u002F":271},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20210326\u002F2926076225\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":245,"date":246,"description":19,"extension":247,"lang":248,"meta":249,"navigation":103,"path":250,"readingMinutes":251,"seo":252,"standalone":253,"stem":254,"tags":255,"tldr":259,"updated":259,"url":260,"__hash__":261},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fbody-parser-deprecated-fix.md","Fixing body-parser Marked as Deprecated","5260762629",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":241},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,30,33,36,39,42,168,171,237],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"While working with Express recently I noticed body-parser is now marked as deprecated. Here's a note on how to resolve it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"body-parser-deprecated","body-parser deprecated",[17,25,26],{},[27,28],"img",{"alt":23,"src":29},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002Fimage.png",[17,31,32],{},"The fix is easy, but worth a note on why it shows up.",[17,34,35],{},"body-parser mainly helps us handle HTTP request data — in plain English, form data. Express v3.x actually had body-parser support built in, but we kept using the third-party package anyway. Once Express v4.x came out, VSCode started flagging it as deprecated.",[17,37,38],{},"You just need to tweak the code slightly.",[17,40,41],{},"Original code:",[43,44,49],"pre",{"className":45,"code":46,"language":47,"meta":48,"style":48},"language-js sh